---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout>
  <main>
    <section class="text-gray-600 body-font flex">
      <div class="container mx-auto flex px-4 py-12 mb-8 md:flex-row flex-col items-center">
        <div class="lg:flex-grow md:w-1/2 lg:pr-24 md:pr-16 flex flex-col md:items-start md:text-left mb-16 md:mb-0 items-center text-center">
          <h1 class="title-font sm:text-4xl text-3xl mb-4 font-medium text-gray-900">
            Print your postage labels in bulk
            <br class="hidden lg:inline-block" /> just like that
          </h1>
          <p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">
            This tool has been built out of annoyance for single-page labels.<br class="mb-1" /> It takes your Royal Mail, Ebay and ParcelForce PDFs with one label per page and creates neat, immediately printable A4 pages with <strong>four</strong> labels on each page. Easy. Done.
          </p>
          <div class="flex justify-center mb-8">
            <a href="/print">
              <button class="cursor-pointer inline-flex text-gray-900 bg-gray-100 shadow-md border-0 py-2 px-6 focus:outline-none hover:bg-gray-200 rounded text-lg">Print some labels!</button>
            </a>
          </div>
          <p class="leading-relaxed text-lg"><span class="font-semibold">Privately</span>, in your browser.</p>
          <p class="leading-relaxed text-lg">No server-side PDF processing, <span class="font-semibold">no file uploads.</span></p>
          <p class="leading-relaxed text-lg"><span class="font-semibold">Open Source</span>, available on <a href="https://github.com/MNeverOff/postlabel">GitHub</a>.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="lg:max-w-lg lg:w-full md:w-1/2 w-5/6">
          <img src="/landing-image-01-compressed.png" width="512" height="512" class="object-cover object-center rounded" alt="Image showing many single-label pages turning to a page with many labels" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="text-gray-600 bg-slate-100 body-font">
      <div class="container px-4 py-12 mb-8 mx-auto">
        <div class="text-center mb-8">
          <h2 class="sm:text-3xl text-2xl font-medium text-center title-font text-gray-900 mb-4">How it works</h2>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed xl:w-2/4 lg:w-3/4 mx-auto">If you want to know how to print Royal Mail, Ebay or ParcelForce labels in bulk on one A4 page - read on! This tool allows you to take single-label pages that Royal Mail, Ebay and ParcelForce create by default and merge them on an A4 page for easy printing.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center lg:w-3/5 mx-auto border-b pb-10 mb-10 border-gray-200 sm:flex-row flex-col">
          <div class="sm:w-32 sm:h-32 h-20 w-20 sm:mr-10 inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-500 flex-shrink-0">
            <svg fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" class="sm:w-16 sm:h-16 w-10 h-10" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path d="M20 11.08V8l-6-6H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16c0 1.1.9 2 2 2h6" /><path d="M14 3v5h5M18 21v-6M15 18h6" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="flex-grow sm:text-left text-center mt-6 sm:mt-0">
            <h3 class="text-gray-900 text-lg title-font font-medium mb-2">Upload the PDFs</h3>
            <p class="leading-relaxed text-base">You take your PDF files and upload them all. You can upload multiple files and each file can have multiple pages. They can mix and match between Royal Mail, Ebay and ParcelForce.</p>
            <a class="mt-3 text-indigo-500 inline-flex items-center" href="/about">
              Learn More
              <svg fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" class="w-4 h-4 ml-2" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"></path>
              </svg>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center lg:w-3/5 mx-auto border-b pb-10 mb-10 border-gray-200 sm:flex-row flex-col">
          <div class="flex-grow sm:text-left text-center mt-6 sm:mt-0">
            <h3 class="text-gray-900 text-lg title-font font-medium mb-2">The ✨ Magic ✨ happens</h3>
            <p class="leading-relaxed text-base">PostLabel takes your PDFs, scans them page by page, detects which type of page it sees (between RM, RM International, Ebay and ParcelForce) using some very dumb text detection, then it chops it out and saves as an image to use in the next step.</p>
            <a class="mt-3 text-indigo-500 inline-flex items-center" href="/about">
              Learn More
              <svg fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" class="w-4 h-4 ml-2" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"></path>
              </svg>
            </a>
          </div>
          <div class="sm:w-32 sm:order-none order-first sm:h-32 h-20 w-20 sm:ml-10 inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-500 flex-shrink-0">
            <svg fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" class="sm:w-16 sm:h-16 w-10 h-10" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <circle cx="6" cy="6" r="3"></circle>
              <circle cx="6" cy="18" r="3"></circle>
              <path d="M20 4L8.12 15.88M14.47 14.48L20 20M8.12 8.12L12 12"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center lg:w-3/5 mx-auto sm:flex-row flex-col">
          <div class="sm:w-32 sm:h-32 h-20 w-20 sm:mr-10 inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-500 flex-shrink-0">
            <svg fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" class="sm:w-16 sm:h-16 w-10 h-10" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <polyline points="6 9 6 2 18 2 18 9"></polyline><path d="M6 18H4a2 2 0 0 1-2-2v-5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h16a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v5a2 2 0 0 1-2 2h-2"></path><rect x="6" y="14" width="12" height="8"></rect>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="flex-grow sm:text-left text-center mt-6 sm:mt-0">
            <h3 class="text-gray-900 text-lg title-font font-medium mb-2">Combined PDF is ready - download or print?</h3>
            <p class="leading-relaxed text-base">After running the tool you'll get an option first to check how the detection and cropping worked and subsequently to download or print a page with your postal labels in bulk, four per page, on however many pages it took.</p>
            <a class="mt-3 text-indigo-500 inline-flex items-center" href="/about">
              Learn More
              <svg fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" class="w-4 h-4 ml-2" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"></path>
              </svg>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="text-gray-600 body-font">
      <div class="container px-4 py-12 mx-auto">
        <div class="text-center mb-6">
          <h2 class="sm:text-3xl text-2xl font-medium text-center title-font text-gray-900 mb-4">Disclaimers & Acknowledgements</h2>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed xl:w-2/4 lg:w-3/4 mx-auto">This tool doesn't collect your files — everything is processed in memory in your browser. There's no file storage. Aggregate product analytics may be collected without PDF contents. Go to the <a href="/legal/tldr">Legal Section</a> for more articulate details.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap lg:w-4/5 sm:mx-auto sm:mb-2 -mx-2">
          <div class="p-2 sm:w-1/2 w-full">
            <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded flex p-4 h-full items-center">
              <svg fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="3" class="text-indigo-500 w-6 h-6 flex-shrink-0 mr-4" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path d="M22 11.08V12a10 10 0 11-5.93-9.14"></path>
                <path d="M22 4L12 14.01l-3-3"></path>
              </svg>
              <span class="title-font font-medium">No storage of your PDF data whatsoever</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="p-2 sm:w-1/2 w-full">
            <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded flex p-4 h-full items-center">
              <svg fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="3" class="text-indigo-500 w-6 h-6 flex-shrink-0 mr-4" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path d="M22 11.08V12a10 10 0 11-5.93-9.14"></path>
                <path d="M22 4L12 14.01l-3-3"></path>
              </svg>
              <span class="title-font font-medium">PDFs never uploaded — processing stays in your browser</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="p-2 sm:w-1/2 w-full">
            <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded flex p-4 h-full items-center">
              <svg fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="3" class="text-indigo-500 w-6 h-6 flex-shrink-0 mr-4" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path d="M22 11.08V12a10 10 0 11-5.93-9.14"></path>
                <path d="M22 4L12 14.01l-3-3"></path>
              </svg>
              <span class="title-font font-medium">There's also no accounts or sessions</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="p-2 sm:w-1/2 w-full">
            <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded flex p-4 h-full items-center">
              <svg fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="3" class="text-indigo-500 w-6 h-6 flex-shrink-0 mr-4" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path d="M22 11.08V12a10 10 0 11-5.93-9.14"></path>
                <path d="M22 4L12 14.01l-3-3"></path>
              </svg>
              <span class="title-font font-medium">Always check your files before print</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="p-2 sm:w-1/2 w-full">
            <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded flex p-4 h-full items-center">
              <svg fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="3" class="text-indigo-500 w-6 h-6 flex-shrink-0 mr-4" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path d="M22 11.08V12a10 10 0 11-5.93-9.14"></path>
                <path d="M22 4L12 14.01l-3-3"></path>
              </svg>
              <span class="title-font font-medium">Open Source, see <a href="https://github.com/MNeverOff/postlabel">GitHub</a></span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="p-2 sm:w-1/2 w-full">
            <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded flex p-4 h-full items-center">
              <svg fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="3" class="text-indigo-500 w-6 h-6 flex-shrink-0 mr-4" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path d="M22 11.08V12a10 10 0 11-5.93-9.14"></path>
                <path d="M22 4L12 14.01l-3-3"></path>
              </svg>
              <span class="title-font font-medium">Aggregate analytics only — no PDF contents or PII collected</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center">
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed xl:w-2/4 lg:w-3/4 mx-auto pt-2">
            Cheers to <a href="https://vercel.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Vercel</a> for free hosting, <a href="https://github.com/mertJF/tailblocks" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Mert Cukuren</a> for these Tailwind CSS templates and <a href="https://github.com/mozilla/pdf.js" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Mozilla</a> with <a href="https://github.com/parallax/jsPDF" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">James Hall</a> for pdf processing libs and many others for wonderful things like React, file-saver package and so on and so forth.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
